caption: Always good.
Loves the atmosphere! I ordered a lunch combo came with soup and half sandwich. Potato soup was amazing! The sandwich was light on the meat other than that not remarkable. Staff were great

5/5 would recommend to anyone in Louisville!! They were so considerate, kind and absolutely so warm and lovely! Everything was exceptionally clean and the food was delicious! The owner was incredibly kind, thoughtful and attentive. Will definitely stop back next time through!
Awesome place to grab lunch. Great food and great staff.
owners cool, great decor, great food
The staff was very friendly! Food was amazing and at a good price! The atmosphere definitely made this a memorable experience! Thank you
Delicious homemade food.
Always delish. Thursday is cheesy soup and croissants. My favorite! Staff is nice. Place is clean.
Great service from David and his team! Traveling from VA and glad we found this place for a quick Reuben, Chicken salad, chili and cheesecake! Stop here for lunch!
Great little lunch spot

Hurray! The Main Eatery is open! Good lunches offered: the chicken noodle soup was rich and tasty; husband's roast beef sandwich and my chicken salad sandwich were fresh and plentiful. Attractive atmosphere and friendly staff. Highly recommend!

Honestly the sandwiches were nothing to write home about. The "cracked wheat bread" which sounds fancy, is just wheat bread you buy at your local grocery store. Then the sandwich meat, lettuce, cheese, all can be bought then made at home. The atmosphere was cool, and the service great

Great place to go for lunch. Soups and sandwiches are fresh and tasty. Personally love the Chili and Broccoli Cheddar Soup. Blue Plate specials are unique especially on Tuesday and Wednesday. The roast beef sandwich on Tuesday is my favorite sandwich in town. Plus the owners and staff are always extremely personable and friendly!
Good food and reasonable prices.
The food was good and the building was clean. Reasonable prices for downtown.
Great food, specials and combos.   Great lunch place on Main St.
Always tastes great
Food is great, good people, fast service and a very comfortable atmosphere.

A fine shop to get delicious sandwiches and soups. The owner is very inviting and engaging. The place is small, but well kept. If it is busy during lunch time there may be a small line which is a testimony to the popularity of the establishment.
Great home recipe soups.
Excellent food, great atmosphere
Loved the food!  Homemade soups were excellent.  I had the broccoli cheese soup and loved it.  The owner was so friendly and helpful.  Lovely experience!
The Best downtown

Love this Place! They've got it down to a science. Always going to see a line out the door, for all the right reasons. They have an ample selection, and an intelligently structured menu . They make your food promptly and with love every time. A great place to eat in or carry out.
Great atmosphere,  great food and great service

I am so grateful we came across this restaurant for lunch while in town.  Great service, quaint atmosphere, snazzy music, delicious food.  Highly recommend the Tuna sandwich and garden vegetable soup!
Great place to grab a reasonably priced lunch!
Excellent sandwiches and we met the owner, he was very kind and helpful on our way through town!

(Translated by Google) Great place to eat cheaply. You can take a set of salad and half a sandwich for $ 9, and there are different soups for another $ 3-4. There are also drinks to choose from. And inside sooooo very polite staff. The cashier finds and talks to each approach. A cool guy is also standing at the distribution, very cheerful and kindly talking. In general, comfortable. And the view from the window is calm.  (Original) Отличное место, чтобы недорого покушать. Можно взять сет из салата и половины сэндвича за 9$, и есть разные супы еще за 3-4$. Напитки тоже на выбор есть. А внутри оооочень вежливый персонал. Кассир к каждому подход находит и болтает. На раздаче тоже классный парень стоит, очень весело и по-доброму разговаривает. В общем, уютно. И вид из окна спокойный.

We ate here for lunch, upon the advice of a local.  My Kentucky ham sandwich was substantial.   My husband liked his chicken salad sandwich. The soups - clam chowder and vegetable beef - excellent!  The plain old iced tea was especially appreciated.   And I liked how the drink came with the special.
i looove their broccoli and cheddar soup! but they were out of it so i got the chili and peanut butter and jelly sandwich instead and dude honestly im soo glad i did cause it was delicious!
Delicious food. Friendly staff. Fair prices.

I've been coming to Main Eatery for 9 years. I've never had a bad experience. The food is consistently on point and the service is great, the owners run their restaurant like a well-oiled machine.  **Hint** On Thursdays, the blue plate special is a chicken salad sandwich on a croissant (buttery and flaky), chips, a drink AND cheesecake!!! All for just $10.55 if you pay with card, you get a small discount when you pay with cash. Enjoy!
Staple! Great lunch spot. Me and my wife love it.
Friendly staff and fast service. Food was great too!
Really good homemade food.  The owner was very helpful and friendly.  Great quality and nice serving size for the price.  We will be back.  Great local owned find!!!
One of my favorite lunch spots downtown!  Great food and reasonably priced which sometimes can be a rare find downtown.
A lovely little quaint place it serves great food and a great lunch experience
Delicious food, great atmosphere. Definitely a long line around lunchtime so come early!
Friendly environment,  delicious menu!

Quant little place enough table seating for abou 80 to 100 I'm estimating.  Excellent menu with everything on the menu being super delicious.  Owners are great people who care about the customer and the experience while you are there...  I would highly recommend this place great food and atmosphere.
Good food. Great ambience.
Cozy diner type restaurant. Excellent service.  I've only tried their grilled cheese and tomato soup thus far which is delicious, but that leaves them at 4 stars for now

It's always a joy to walk into the tiny entryway of the Main Eatery to be greeted by sunlight, plants, and Billy Joel. Music. Not himself, unfortunately, although this is just the kind of bread he'd like put in his jar. The service is phenomenal, the menu is clear and *everywhere* so no matter where you are in line you can debate over the cheap & delicious combos they offer. Like, the homemade-croissant chicken salad sandwich & soup vs. the BLT and tomato bisque. Basically, you can't go wrong, and you'll be full long before your wallet's empty. My favorite part is probably the seating, though: this place is E NOR MOUS once you're inside, with the best little indoor balcony -- many paintings, many plants -- perched next to the window, so you can eat in the sunlight (or watching the rain). I'll keep coming back for the longest time. ... I'm sorry, okay, I'm done x)
Very clean, fast, affordable and friendly service.  The soups and sandwiches we're great and just what we needed!
Great little lunch spot! Especially if you work around the area and can get there before noon. The service reminds me of Chic Fil-A. Real friendly atmosphere!😉👍
amazing food great service. will definitely be back

love this place! always have delicious soups and sandwiches the environment is always friendly the service is fast. and this place has a unique layout with upstairs sitting area to eat and look out the window  on to the busy streets of downtown. I always love to go here.
Fantastic sandwiches. Nice atmosphere with lots of plants.
Always great food and courteous service
This place is amazing! The food was very good. The soup was amazing. Definitely recommend. Very friendly staff.

Great soup and sandwiches. One of my favorite lunch spots when I'm working downtown. The staff are very friendly. I recommend getting here a few minutes before noon to avoid the long line of people wanting their tasty fare for lunch

On a trip through Louisville we stopped here.  The food was fantastic the environment was nice. Establishment was clean friendly and efficient.  If we come back through i would def look this place up!
Its fresh everyday!
Good and delicious!
The food was healthy, amazing and so fresh! Recommend and will be going back. The people were great. So happy to have discovered this inner city gem

This is my favorite lunch spot.  The staff is friendly and helpful.  The food is always fresh and amazing.  They do a daily blue plate special with a good deal for a tasty lunch.  My favorite is the Thursday special which is chicken salad on a freshly made croissant, chips, and fresh cheese cake.  The line can get long around noon, but you will understand why once you get your food.   5 stars all day!
The cheeseburgers are best I've ever tasted if you get either or fries or chilli you might as well get both
Very good sandwiches and chili.
Cozy place to grab a sandwich, soup or salad! The guy who takes order is so friendly! I did not read you have to order by number - oops! Love the multi tier layout and cool stained glass!

This place never let's me down. Never had a bad meal here. Reubens are delicious. Had the chili for the first time today and it was fantastic. Highly recommend going on a Thursday and getting their Blue Plate Special. It comes with chicken salad on a homemade croissant, chips or soup, and some killer cheesecake.
Nice place, good food
A great price on great food!
Amazing food
My lunchtime favorite. A delicious regular rotation of specials, and a standard soup and sandwich menu that you can’t go wrong with.
I tried the Reuben and some broccoli cheese soup, both which we're really good and reasonably priced.
Good food, slow service
Nice place great food and atmosphere
Great soup selection..good sandwich fixins..good price..friendly staff..very casual
Great sandwiches and soup.
Very friendly atmosphere. The wait was worth it. Very good food for the price!
Food was great.  Very friendly
Nice place with good food for a good price. Employees were very nice and friendly.
Amazing!  Food was super yummy and staff was super nice.
Personable staff and great food
Customer service is amazing and great quality food.
Great vegetable soup and grilled cheese
Fresh food and yummy.  Always friendly and clean.
Great food but the guy at the register talks too long. Long lines
Very nice little eatery cafe. Food was wonderful and just enough for a little lunch!!👌
I just started working downtown and I went in to grab the special and I love the atmosphere. Great hometown feel. The cashier felt like a longtime friend.
Perfect for lunch downtown. I'm jealous that this place isn't closer to where I work. So delicious in there.

Always friendly. I love Thursdays special (chicken salad on a croissant with chips, a drink, and cheesecake with raspberry drizzle and grated chocolate) for under $10. Hands down the best deal in the city for lunch. Other things on the menu are delicious and enjoy the huge variety of sandwiches and soups.
Highly recommend going to thursday. The blue plate special is chicken salad on a croissant and it is very good.

Only open for lunch. The worst thing about The Main Eatery is that the line is always very long. I highly recommend the blue plate specials. Thursday is a chicken salad on a fresh baked croissant. It is fantastic.
The food is always delicious and the service is quick, friendly, and excellent.
What a great lunch spot!  Good selection of items at a very reasonable price. Food was wonderful and atmosphere perfect for lunch time.
You can tell care and consideration has been put into everything they serve.  Great staff, very nice seating areas.
High quality soup & sandwich lunch-only restaurant.  The food is outstanding, but so are the people!
Atmosphere is energetic, extremely fast service, and their food is fabulous!
It's so good, definitely recommend to all.
Great food
The food is simple and good. The prices seem too expensive for the portion sizes.

Dave and staff are amazing. By time you order your food and pay they almost have it packed and ready to go. Quality has always been top notch. I recommend Thursday's blue plate Chicken Salad on croissant with cheesecake. Portion sizes are on point with cost, most of the time I take a little back to the office with me. My wife really likes their soups.

Great place to stop in for lunch downtown. Wide variety of tasty sandwich options. There's usually a line at lunch, but it moves pretty steadily, and the food is prepared quickly. Be advised: while they will accept credit cards, they prefer cash. If you can stop by an ATM where you won't get a fee charged, it's recommend to grab a little cash before ordering.
Good joint! Locally owned by some recovering New Yorkers. :) Good selections and great prices. This place is a favorite go to for lunch.
Pretty good food. Locally owned sandwich shop. If you want to reenact a Seinfeld scene, ask for a substitution or special order.
Amazing lunch spot. Owners a great. Always friendly. Much of the food is made in house or specifically for them. I love it.
Cafeteria style soup and sandwich kinda place. Lots of regulars here, friendly and fresh food.
Staff is amazing and super friendly. I felt welcomed here even as they were closing. Food is amazing. Best deli I've been to in louisville hands down
Great food and price. Totally recommended
Absolutely a lovely place !! Brilliant food and humorous kind customer service .
Great sandwich and soup shop! Lots off options and daily specials.

Ate late lunch there today with my three young children after visiting the KY science center.  The owner helped by recommending things the kids would like and helped me decide that I didn't need the (more expensive) combo option for each order. I appreciated that! Made us feel very welcome. Discretely asked me if it was ok to give the kids a cookie as a reward for being well-behaved during lunch.  Great feeling and the food was awesome,  too!
Yum
Favorite lunch spot. Great food at a very reasonable price. Service is the best.
Cute place, good food, and a fun time with or without friends! I love it! ^-^
LOVE going here for lunch!  Staff is super friendly, and the food is great!  Prices are reasonable too!
Inexpensive food. Delicious sandwich, chili, and soda for under 10 bucks. Super polite staff. A staple for anyone working downtown.
